<user>101190673522003371284<//user><username>Jerry Yang< /username><Time>1454135668014<//Time><Rating>3< /Rating>< review>
I found out about this place on the Concord newly opened Businesses/restaurants. It is a Mom and Pop place that serves Lunch and Breakfast. It is tuck in a little shopping off of Monument but worth a try. I had tried their Chocolate Malt with the Bacon Cheeseburger minus the fries. The burger was a decent size with Onions (raw), Tomato, Lettuce and  American Cheese and Bacon. The bun was a little bigger than patty but it was okay because it corralled all the ingredients from spilling out.  The bun was also soft. The Chocolate Malt was the Star of the show. Nice thick consistency and not too shabby for $4 something. The price for Burger and Malt was a little over $10 and was perfectly portioned and price point for what you get. Bonus tip; You can "piggyback" free wireless because the Laundromat next door has it.</review>

<Rate>5<//Rate><Text>A couple of weeks ago my wife and I purchased a used 2015 VW Golf Sportwagon at Livermore Honda. At Livermore Honda we were assisted by Aaron and his sales manager, Matt.

Before our purchase, I had contacted several other car dealerships, visited two, and conducted in-depth Internet searches to check available cars and prices in the greater San Francisco Bay Area. It turned out that Livermore Honda had the car and model that we were looking for with low-mileage and at a reasonable price.

Aaron was very helpful in answering our questions, following up to see if we needed any more information, and, when we got down to serious negotiating, he was facilitative in working with Matt to zero in on a mutually agreeable price. We love our new car.

The transaction was not problem-free. The night that we drove the car home we stood admiring our new vehicle and noticed a couple of problems. First, there was a rear license plate but no front plate. Second, the passenger side of the vehicle had no hubcaps. There had been hubcaps on the car in the dealership's ads and we were fairly sure that the car had all four hubcaps when we'd test driven the car.

Fortunately, when I contacted the car dealership the very next day with our concerns, Livermore Honda stood solidly behind the sale. They changed the license plate registration renewal to an order for new plates and they ordered replacement VW hubcaps so that our car would look as-new - both these adjustments were at no additional cost.

Livermore Honda's responsiveness in correcting those issues, even though the car was sold "as is" and we had driven it off the lot, reinforced our perception that - should there be any unexpected problems - it was better to have bought a vehicle from a reliable new and used car dealership such as Livermore Honda than from a private seller or from a used car lot.

We would certainly check out the inventory at Livermore Honda when we are in the market for another car.< /Text><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP6v5h8N1NjZU_f0fa7KxqUN0yG14Mr_Vm4ojUQ=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pics>< response>

I was specifically looking for a used Chevy Suburban and found one that I was interested in at Livermore Honda of all places. I made the trip out there from Fremont and met Dan, the Sales Consultant. He is really friendly and had good knowledge of the vehicle.

After inspecting the vehicle and taking it for a  test drive I made an offer. Not once during this process did I feel pressured to buy. I also decided to see what I could get for a trade-in, and although their initial offer was very low, they did work with me to increase the amount to my satisfaction. <text>Here we go....

I purchased a vehicle from Livermore Honda about a year ago.  The vehicle was a used 2007 Jeep Grand Cherokee Limited with roughly 90K miles. It appeared to be in excellent shape and was sold based on that premise.

To perform my due diligence I requested a copy of the vehicle report which stated the car passed all tests performed at the time prior to placing the vehicle on the lot.

Unfortunately, incompetence, omissions or bad luck have caused this car buying situation to become the biggest nightmare in my life and result in my soured opinion of this dealer.

The vehicle was purchased for around $17,000~ and has officially become the most expensive and biggest piece of @#$!!! of any car that I have purchased in the last 20+ years ( and I have purchased a dozen plus vehicles in that time).

Within 1 week of taking the car off of the lot a broken motor mount was discovered and the catalytic converter failed and had to be replaced.  Livermore Honda paid for 50% of the repair of the motor mount, but accepted no responsibility for the converter.  Those repair cost about $2,000.  Next, within 30 days the vehicle started stalling, was found to have a leaking thermostat housing.  The stalling required several visits, missed diagnoses and ultimately required the entire electrical system to looked at, throttle body replaced and has cost another $1,500~.  Now, roughly a year later and the car at 99K miles, I am told that struts, shocks and other issues have failed and need replacing which will add up to another $1,500~.

Note to self.... NEVER buy another car from this dealership group!!!! EVER!!!  Despite being nice people, the product they put on the road was misrepresented from an implied reliability standpoint.  The result was spending a tremendous amount of money to keep the car safe and on the road and I would have never bought that specific car had this been known or revealed.

Granted buying a car comes with a buyer beware sticker.  But, this has been taken to another extreme that no one should have to encounter.<//text><Pics>None< /Pics>< resp>

<user_id>108097007139793392198<//user_id><Name>Andrew Romich<//Name><date>1487926995258< /date><Rate>1< /Rate>< Review>
BUYER BEWARE!

I recently bought a 2017 Honda Civic from this dealership and was, in the end, given a completely different model than what we had discussed and agreed on! All of my contact with this dealer, and my salesperson, Adryanna, were pertaining to my interest in the EX-T. The only car I test drove was an EX-T. I received price quotes from all over the area for the EX-T with Honda Sensing. (Honda Sensing is an additional safety feature Honda offers that I decided to add.) Adryanna even agreed to match the price, to the dollar, on the better price I received on the EX-T with Honda Sensing from a competing dealership.

At first, they couldn't find the car, and said they would call me when they did.Then, the very next morning, I get a call from Adryanna and she says they found "my car" and she went to pick it up at whatever dealership they got it from and it is now at Livermore Honda. I come in the next day to complete the deal. She shows me the car. I look at it, not thinking I need to check under the hood to verify it is an EX-T, since we only discussed one model the whole time, and I sign the paperwork. I get home, look at my key, and realize it says 2.0L. I know that the turbo is 1.5L. Immediately I call Adryanna, and inform her that my key says 2.0L but I know the turbo is 1.5L, and I ask if it is just marked wrong on the key? She at first says yes. I hang up and then check under the hood myself. Sure enough, it's 2.0L. I call back, and tell her it's not the 1.5L, and that I think there has been a mistake. I immediately take the car back in. The car is an EX and not an EX-T! She then says that I said it was OK to just get the EX with Honda Sensing since they couldn't "find" the EX-T with Honda Sensing. No. And the price we agreed on was for the EX-T with Honda Sensing!!

None of the copies of receipts and documentation I received say EX or EX-T, simply 2017 Honda Civic and a VIN number. From the outside, the EX looks near identical to the EX-T. I didn't think to verify every feature, since we had only discussed ONE model the ENTIRE time. And I even mentioned to her the day she was looking for "my car" how much I loved the turbo. I immediately ask to speak with General Manager (his name is AJ). I explain all of the details to the GM, and he simply says "you signed the paperwork and bought the car" and that "this is the car you wanted." Keep in mind I had not spoken with him at all until now! Are you kidding me?? At this point, I am completely floored by what I am hearing. I show him all of the emails and all of our correspondence which only mentions EX-T. Not to mention, the only price quote we talked about, and the one they matched, to the dollar, was for an EX-T with Honda Sensing. If they thought I was fine with a different model, why would they think I was fine paying that same price for a lower model?! The GM then tells me he can't take the car back because now it's a used car and he will lose money, but all he can do is either give me $100 back or 2 free services. You gave me a different car than what I agreed on! (And, also, researching after the fact what an EX with Honda Sensing should cost, it's really about $600 difference.) I relay all of this to the Assistant to the Owner (surely, he will listen). But no! He simply dismisses this, through his Assistant, and refuses to speak with me. I just poured $23K into your dealership for a different car than what I received, and you won't even have the decency to speak with me about the issue?! The only one that truly showed compassion for the situation was the Owner's Assistant, Lana. I'm still in shock that my salesperson (Adryanna), the GM (AJ), and the Owner (Michael Walsh) did very little to rectify this situation, or admit their own fault.

I'm not sure if I was purposely scammed, or simply a victim of extremely poor service. Either way, this was an egregious mistake, and I will be taking this to Honda corporate, the BBB, and, if needed, my lawyer.<//Review>

I had no idea what this place was when entering but stood amazed as soon as I walked through the door. There are SOOOO many drinks options from teas to snows to milks, and a small selection of food to boot. I was flabbergasted when my just mixed (delicious) Thai Tea with Honey Boba came with a just-sealed plastic film on top, perfect for poking a straw through. The staff were so friendly, patient and helpful when I explained I had no idea what to get. They let me taste things and made a great suggestion. I will be back!!!</Text>

<username>julie limbaugh<//username><time>1531094250011< /time><rating>4< /rating>< Text>
It was good. We went with family who eat very clean and organic. We had the Misto board which was 3 cheeses, amazing bread,  two meats, olives, red and green grapes and fig jam. We also shared a Caesar salad and the Ceci bean salad and 2 Margherita pizzas. It was just right for 4 of us, maybe a little too much. We ate a LOT of bread, but the amazing thing is.....we didn't feel stuffed or heavy afterwards. The Caesar was dressed lightly, which was nice on a  warm evening and sitting on the back "porch" was lovely. I would definitely go again when in the area. P.S. Don't forget the chocolate covered Spumoni (a big ball of spumoni covered in a thin  eskimo pie-like shell of delicious chocolate).</Text>

<Name>Sara Klipps</Name>< gmap_id>
0x80dcdbddb075693f:0x818e094c9dd911f6</gmap_id>
<text>This place is such a cute local restaurant, microbrewery, winery. I've been here twice, once for a girls night out and today, for a date night with the hubby.  It's small and they don't take reservations so come early if you don't want to wait. Patio vs inside, I prefer inside since the patio overlooks a parking lot. Free parking in the lot behind the restaurant or free 1 hour parking on the street. They have a nice wine selection from Pozzuoli wine with their vineyard from Paso Robles, I love their Cabernet Sauvignon and Insieme. I've have both the wine sampler and tasting. I prefer the tasting since you can choose what wines. The sampler was ok, love that they served a white wine, Rose, and 2 reds but I only really loved the Rose and one of the reds.... I did enjoy their formaggio (cheese) plate with 4 types of cheese, grapes, hot slices of toasted bread, and olives. It was good, albeit a bit pricey. We fell in love with the goat cheese with chives and onion and bought an extra side for $4 to take home! Their microbrewery has a small but good selection of beer brewed on-site. Today, they were out of some of their beers so my husband tried their Avery White ale which is a guest ale, which was nice and light. They have an in-house honey cream ale which I would love to try next time it's available!

The last time I came here, the girls and I ordered a bruschetta appetizer which was amazing and their pizzas. We ordered an eggplant pizza which was so thinly sliced and fresh and light. Their salad was also delicious. Overall, a cute local spot to hang out, either for girls night, date night, or with friends. I can't wait to introduce more friends to this spot! Love their food, wine, and beer selection!<//text>< Rate>

<gmapID>0x80dcdbddb075693f:0x818e094c9dd911f6< /gmapID></record></dataset><record>
< Resp>
None</Resp>
< Text>
Big news for beer and wine drinkers in Tustin. Centro, a winery and microbrewery, is now open in Old Town Tustin.

The brewery-restaurant is owned by Pozzuoli Vineyard & Winery, which is located in Paso Robles. (How often do you see a winery that lists its two locations as someplace in wine country, and Tustin?) Pazzuoli opened a tasting room in Tustin a couple of years ago at 15481 Red Hill Avenue, and now has opened this impressive location in Old Town Tustin.

I'm a wine fan, but what really got me excited about this place is the microbrewery. They call the beer side of the operation Archaic Craft Brewery. I visited on opening day, and they had four beers on tap, but only one was created in house, and that was the Honey Kolsch. If the Honey Kolsch is any indication of the brews we can expect from Archaic, then this place will be great for beer drinkers. It was a great German style Kolsch, with good mouth feel and no harsh aftertaste.

This is a true family business, with Enrico Pozzuoli as the winemaker, and his son Sandro Pozzuoli handling the brewmaster duties. I spent some time with Sandro discussing the beers he is brewing. His knowledge was apparent, and I was impressed that, even though he wanted to roll out a beer or two more for the grand opening, he held back because they weren't yet where he wanted them to be. Look for an IPA soon.

I'm hoping they will expand the number of available beers on tap. Certainly, if they want to make this a destination for microbrewery crawlers, they'll need a greater selection. But how many beers can you really drink? For now, live with four, and go to Centro to check out the impressive modern/rustic interior.

As to the food, we tried the Margherita pizza ($9) and the Hummus plate ($8) (we dug into hummus plate so quickly, we forgot to take a picture; picture above shows cheese plate ordered by another patron). Both were excellent. The pizzas are baked in a wood-fired oven. They also offer cheese plates, salads, paninis, and desserts.

Beers were $6 and $7 a pint, and the wine ranged from $10 to $15 a glass. Personal pizzas cost about $10 to $14. Some pizza is available by the slice for $4. If you like the beer, you can take a 32 or 64-ounce growler to go.

Centro is a great addition to Old Town Tustin. Be sure to give it a try.< /Text>

<text>First visit, went to see Berlin. Doors opened 35 minutes late, they let people without tickets go in first, which made a few people in line go nuts. Worse, once inside we were told the concert didn't start until 11pm (our sitter was livid); I suppose that's how they make their money since drinks are $10 each.

<Rating>5<//Rating><gmapID>0x80dd2bcd4eec5cb7:0xe357ba00250f64df<//gmapID><Pics>None<//Pics><review>The best 80s venue around! The decor is fantastic, with great 80s icons painted in neon on the walls lit by blacklights to really add to the vibe. The music is always good, and there are TVs around the dance floor showing music videos for the songs playing. They also have a stage where various live bands come in to perform. They have great cover bands that come through and different themed nights. Dressing up in 80s themed attire is encouraged! This is also a fairly safe place to go and have a good time, as typically the crowd here is a little older and just out for a drink or two and dancing.

Parking is not easy though, as they have a small lot! I recommend parking at the Fullerton Park and Ride down the street, and just walking the block and a half to the club. They are also cash only for the $10 cover charge after 9pm, so plan accordingly or be ready to use their atm in the corner.</review>< Name>
Adri M<//Name>

Mark Stebbins<//user_name>
< Rating>
3< /Rating>
< GmapID>
0x80dd2bcd4eec5cb7:0xe357ba00250f64df<//GmapID>
<pics>None</pics>< text>
Atsmophere was fun and the music was great of course.  Parking filled up fast so we paid $10 to park across the street.  The lot attendant was a crack up and rapped to us because I was wearing my RUN DMC gear.
The dance floor was totally packed, which I don't mind, but some people tend to lose their spatial awareness after a few drinks.  The service is very slow, most  likely due to being understaffed.  It took almost 2 hours to get our food and first drink and we showed up at 7pm when they opened.  Our waitress was nice and comped one of our drinks but it wasn't her fault so we tipped her well.  Overall,  the experience was fun and I would go back.  If you go, make the effort to wear your best 80's clothes.  It was so much more fun that way.  But again, definitely eat beforehand or your night may not start off so well.</text>

<name>Tad Mukai</name>< time>
1517673966475< /time>
<rating>5</rating>< Text>
Wanna go back in time?  Visit the Totally 80s Bar and Grille and the music, old school cabinet video games, murals of 80s icons on the walls, and music videos shown on the monitors throughout the joint will make you feel like you stepped out of Doc Brown's DeLorean into a time when Ronald Reagan is President, the Raiders call L.A. their home, and Oingo Boingo is still performing together.
The DJs spin all the best 80s new wave and dance music and the dance floor gets packed.  Also, you can occasionally see your favorite 80s bands perform is this intimate venue.  The menu is not expansive, but the food is good.  The drinks all have great 80s names like "the Thriller" and "the Pac Man".  This is a cool place to visit, so wear your best 80s attire if you want the full experience.< /Text>

<pictures>None</pictures><Text>First timer to this place, went this past Saturday for a friend's birthday.

The positive: Great 80's music, good space to dance. Not pretentious at all since the dress code is pretty lax. This put me at ease to dance the night away and not think so much about what I or anyone else was wearing. It didn't feel like as much of a meat market as other clubs/bars.

They had a live band going. They were meh. The DJ was better on this particular night.

So 2 reasons why this place gets 3 stars from me:

1) Parking SUCKS. The place seems to have 2 small parking lots that are part of the property, one on the side of the restaurant, right on Orangethorpe. Their other lot is right behind the restaurant/club. If you can score parking here, it's free, no problem. But for the majority of us partygoers who tend to arrive a little more fashionably late, there are a couple of privately owned lots around the club that charge whatever they want. We ended up having to paying $10 to park in the dirt lot next door, which seemed like too much because this is Fullerton and not Vegas (no dirt lots in Vegas, that's for sure!), but it was convenient. My recommendation is to just Uber or Lyft it to this place. Probably what we'll do next time.

2) I had to spend WAY too much to even get a buzz going...drinks were pretty weak. They charged me extra to make my drink a little more stiff. Maybe it was just the one bartender we had.

Other than that, if you want a laid back place to shake it all night, then come here.</Text><user>105338556797631607610<//user>< name>
Veronica Gonzalez<//name>

<Text>Go to the 80s bar in Pamona or LA instead!!! The service is terrible.came here for my birthday,  BIG MISTAKE.  Ordered food and soda from our table at 802pm got our sodas at 830 and our food items came at 904. Which i had then asked for ketchup amd salsa, that took another 23 minutes. By then our food was cold. We went up to the crowded bar, ordered drinnks and came back with drinks and our waitress STILL hadnt come to our table with refills.

Also dont order the grilled cheese it was terrible! The bread tastes like cheap overtoasted white bread and barely any cheese. The nachos are ocerpriced for the portion and look like something i could make for myself at home. Also the tacos dont come with salsa so expect to eat cold tacos if you want salsa. Amd expect to eat cold tatertots if you want ketchup.

If you order food and drinks expect bad service with mediocre food.
got up to take a picture less then 10 feet away and the waitress gave away one of our tables and nust moved our things over to our other one and WE HADN'T EVEN GOTTEN OUR FOOD YET! Never going back. Each had to pay 10$ cover to wait over an hour for food and over 20 minutes just for refills. Also by the time we actually finished eating it was so packed with a way older drunk crowd that there wasnt even room to dance. We left and spent. the rest of our night somewhere else. I wouldn't waste your time or money going here.< /Text><Date>1463445057424<//Date><Name>Katie Aileen<//Name><resp>None< /resp></record>
